Source: cdrom-detect
Section: debian-installer
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian Install System Team <debian-boot@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Raphael Hertzog <hertzog@debian.org>, Tollef Fog Heen <tfheen@debian.org>, Petter Reinholdtsen <pere@debian.org>
Build-Depends-Indep: debhelper (>= 4.1.13), dpkg-dev (>= 1.7.0), po-debconf (>= 0.5.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: cdrom-detect
Architecture: all
Depends: cdebconf-udeb (>= 0.31), modutils-basic | modutils-full, hw-detect
XB-Installer-Menu-Item: 15
Description: Detect CDROM devices and mount the CD in /cdrom
 This udeb will try to detect CDROM device. It will automatically insert
 the corresponding modules in the kernel and will mount the
 Debian Installation CD on /cdrom.
 .
 cdrom-detect is a minimal package used by debian-installer.
